The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                               Good Morning
      Hello It's Friday , March 21 , 2008                    
	Holi     Kirtan, drama and bhog at the Iskcon headquarters on Albert Road, 9am to 8.30pm    
	Restriction    Dont move around in trucks playing with colour.    Dont throw colour at people unwilling to play and police and army officers.    Dont carry arms or crackers while taking part in processions.    Buses and trams will be off the road till 1pm.    Processions cannot be taken out on CR Avenue, Jyotindra Mohan Avenue and Bhupen Bose Avenue between 8am and 10pm.    Processions cannot be taken out on March 21 from 7am to 1pm and on March 22 from 2pm to 9pm on Keshub Sen Street, College Street, MG Road, Zakaria Street, portions of Rabindra Sarani, Eden Hospital Road, Phoolbagan Road, Watgunge Road, Ekbalpore Road, Bhupen Bose Avenue, Dr Subir Bose Road, Jyotindra Mohan Avenue, Gurusaday Road, AJC Bose Road, Rawdon Street, Shakespeare Sarani, Ballygunge Circular Road, SN Banerjee Road, JL Nehru Road, a portion of Park Street and in the BBD Bag area.     
	Yatra    Sankirtan Yatra celebrating Abirbhav Mahotsav of Sri Chaitanya Mahaprabhu. Procession to start from Raja Subodh Mullick Square, 7.30am.    
	Music    Ajoy Ray to present jazz videos, audios and talks by eminent jazz personalities at Calcutta School of Music, 7pm.    
	Art watch    Inauguration of an exhibition of photographs by Nawajesh Ahmed on Bangladesh at Weavers Studio Centre for the Arts, 6pm.                                                                                                                                                                   
